# 🎯 Smart Pricing Engine

[![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.9+-blue.svg)](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
[![Streamlit](https://img.shields.io/badge/Streamlit-1.28+-red.svg)](https://streamlit.io/)
[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)

**ML-Powered Demand Forecasting & Price Optimization**

An end-to-end machine learning application that predicts product demand at different price points and identifies revenue-maximizing prices through price elasticity analysis.

![App Screenshot](screenshots/price_optimizer.png)
<!-- Add screenshots folder with images of your app -->

💼 Business Impact
The Problem

Retailers lose revenue through suboptimal pricing decisions.
If prices are set too high, sales volume declines. If prices are too low, profit margins are left on the table. Managing optimal prices across thousands of products is difficult to do manually and often leads to inconsistent pricing strategies.

The Solution

This machine learning pricing engine analyzes transactional retail data to estimate demand sensitivity and identify potential pricing opportunities.

Using the Online Retail II dataset (1M+ transactions), the model identified:

Metric	Result
Products analyzed	50
Products with pricing opportunities	86%
Average simulated revenue uplift	+258%
Highest single-product opportunity	+781%

These estimates are generated through demand simulation using an XGBoost demand model combined with price elasticity analysis.

Real Example

A decorative retail item priced at £1.25 was identified as having inelastic demand.
Simulation suggested that increasing the price to £1.88 would have minimal impact on demand while significantly increasing revenue per unit.

Business Interpretation

This type of analysis enables retailers to:

• Identify products with underpriced demand
• Adjust pricing based on demand sensitivity
• Improve revenue without increasing marketing spend

By systematically applying this approach across an entire product catalog, retailers can move from static pricing strategies to data-driven price optimization.

---

## 🚀 Features

- **Demand Prediction** — ML models predict weekly product demand based on price and contextual features
- **Price Elasticity Analysis** — Calculate how sensitive each product's demand is to price changes
- **Revenue Optimization** — Identify the price point that maximizes revenue
- **Interactive Dashboard** — Explore data, compare models, and simulate pricing scenarios
- **Real-Time Predictions** — Adjust price slider and instantly see predicted demand

---

## 📊 Results

| Model | RMSE | MAE | R² |
|-------|------|-----|-----|
| Baseline (Mean) | 149.56 | 68.63 | -0.003 |
| **Linear Regression** | **120.69** | 50.94 | **0.347** |
| Random Forest | 122.75 | 49.54 | 0.324 |
| XGBoost | 130.12 | 47.12 | 0.241 |

**Key Findings:**
- All ML models significantly outperformed baseline
- 43 of 50 products analyzed showed >5% revenue uplift potential
- Average potential revenue uplift: 258%

